				<td colspan="2"><span>Could be wrong as I don't play any more (just checking in today to see what's changed), but I think you have it backwards.  The faster you run, the smaller the circle.  When you are running faster, you turn much faster, so smaller circles.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Edit: I was just looking at the guides, and you are right, the autocircle guide says faster speed equals bigger circle, so nevermind my answer.
