				<td colspan="2"><span>The faster you run the larger the circle.  I've always been suspicious that a kitty bard can't auto-circle as well because they present a larger target.  Once I got a TDoK the cougars in Iceclad were easy, it was so simple that it's boring.  A lot is going to depend on the mobs you kite,  if they are fast or have a good melee reach then it not worth the trouble to mess with them.  I usually try to AoE just one of an unfamiliar mob to see how it responds.  If it smacks me more than once when I'm doing a trial run then I leave it alone.</span></td>
